==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Angora
<hw>An*go"ra</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧n*g⟦omac⟧"r⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>A city of Asia Minor (or Anatolia) which has given its name to a
goat, a cat, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Angora cat</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a variety of
the domestic cat with very long and silky hair, generally of the
brownish white color. Called also <altname>Angola cat</altname>. See
<er>Cat</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Angora goat</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>,
<cd>a variety of the domestic goat, reared for its long silky hair,
which is highly prized for manufacture.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Angostura bark</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Angostura</ent>⟦br⟧
